10 An Act relating to the State Department of Health;
making an appropriation; stating purpose; requiring
11 that portions of certain appropriated funds be used
for certain purposes; stating purpose of certain
12 disbursement; requiring the use of certain data;
directing the Department to develop method of
13 disbursement; authorizing promulgation of rules;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
14 emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the State Department
19 of Health from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
20 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
21 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of One Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars
22 ($150,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to carry out
23 the provisions of Enrolled House Bill No. 3644 of the 2nd Session of
24 the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
SB1162 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 SECTION 2. From the funds appropriated to the State Department
2 of Health in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session of the
3 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of One Hundred Fifty Thousand
4 Dollars ($150,000.00) shall be used to maintain sickle cell
5 outreach.
6 SECTION 3. From the funds appropriated to the State Department
7 of Health in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session of the
8 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of One Million Dollars
9 ($1,000,000.00) shall be used to contract with or employ a financial
10 expert to monitor and report to the Legislature the financial well-
11 being of the budget of the Department of Mental Health and Substance
12 Abuse Services.
13 SECTION 4. From the funds appropriated to the State Department
14 of Health in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session of the
15 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Three Million Dollars
16 ($3,000,000.00) shall be disbursed to health centers authorized
17 under Section 330 of the Public Health Service Act, and incorporated
18 in the State of Oklahoma. Any disbursement shall be for the purpose
19 of increasing access to primary health care which may include
20 medical, dental, and/or mental health and substance abuse treatment
21 services in or near designated Medically Underserved Areas or
22 Medically Underserved Populations. Any disbursement for increased
23 access to primary health care services shall be supported by data
24 according to proportions of patient volume and access for the
SB1162 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 unin sured. The method of disbursement shall be developed by the
2 State Department of Health. The State Commissioner of Health is
3 authorized to promulgate the method of disbursement into rules.
4 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
5 SECTION 6. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
6 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
7 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
8 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
9
10 DIRECT TO CALENDAR.
